# <type>(<scope>): <summary>          ← ≤72 chars, imperative ("add", not "added")
#
# <body — what changed and why; wrap ~72 chars. Blank line above.>
#
# <footer — BREAKING CHANGE: <desc>, Closes #123, Co-Authored-By: …>
#
# ── Conventional Commits (see CONTRIBUTING.md → Commit messages) ──────────────
# type:  feat  fix  docs  style  refactor  perf  test  build  ci  chore  revert
# bump:  feat → minor   fix → patch   BREAKING CHANGE / type! → major (SemVer)
# scope: optional, e.g. feat(markdown):  fix(cli):  docs(readme):
# Example:  fix(scroll): thread FRAME_MS through the evaluate() args
